function t.makeProgram(gl,vShader,fShader)
  local program = gl.createProgram()
  local vertShader = gl.createShader(gl.VERTEX_SHADER)
  gl.shaderSource(vertShader,vShader)
  gl.compileShader(vertShader)
  gl.attachShader(program, vertShader)
  local fragShader = gl.createShader(gl.FRAGMENT_SHADER)
  gl.shaderSource(fragShader,fShader)
  gl.compileShader(fragShader)
  gl.attachShader(program, fragShader)

  gl.linkProgram(program)
  local linked = gl.getProgramParameter(
    program, gl.LINK_STATUS
  )
  if not linked then
    local err = gl.getShaderInfoLog(vertShader)
    err = err..\"\\n\"..gl.getShaderInfoLog(fragShader)
    return nil,err
  end
  return program
end"

local touches = r.cursors.touches
touches.registry = {}
function touches.make(touchid)
   local reg = touches.registry
   if not reg[touchid] then
      if not touches.primary then touches.primary = touchid end
      reg[touchid] = {id=touchid}
      return reg[touchid]
   else
      return reg[touchid]
   end
end
function touches.kill(touchid)
   local reg = touches.registry
   if touches.primary and touchid == touches.primary then
      touches.primary = nil
   end
   reg[touchid] = nil
end

function r.setCursor(cursor,event,viewProportions)
   if viewProportions > 1 then
      cursor.x = viewProportions*(event.x)
      cursor.y = event.y
   else
      cursor.x = event.x
      cursor.y = event.y/viewProportions
   end
end

   hovered = {down=\"held\",moveout=\"none\"},
   pulled = {up=\"none\",movein=\"hovered\"},

}

function r.pushCenteredQuad(x,y,wLen,hLen)
   local v,c = r.drawList.verts, r.drawList.colors
   local w,h = wLen/2, hLen/2
   local sc = r.xOverY -- scaling
   local t,b,l,r if 1 > sc then
      t,b,l,r = y+h*sc,y-h*sc,x-w,x+w else
      t,b,l,r = y+h,y-h,x-w/sc,x+w/sc
   end
   local tbl = {l,t, l,b, r,t, r,t, l,b, r,b}
   for i,elem in ipairs(tbl) do table.insert(v, elem) end
   for i=1,6 do
      for i=1,3 do table.insert(c,0.4) end
      table.insert(c,1.0)
   end
end

function r.vpPushQuad(rect)
   local sz = r.vpState.sizeFactor
   local verts,colors = r.drawList.verts, r.drawList.colors
   local sc = r.xOverY -- scaling
   local t,b,l,r = rect.t/sz,rect.b/sz,rect.l/sz,rect.r/sz

   local tbl = {l,t, l,b, r,t, r,t, l,b, r,b}
   for i,vert in ipairs(tbl) do table.insert(verts,vert) end

local gui = state.root.__plugins.Gui

function gui.frame(s,plug)
   --collectgarbage()
   --DOM.log(collectgarbage(\"count\"))
   if gui.hook then gui.hook(s,s.panels[gui.name]) end

   local dpr = DOM.window.devicePixelRatio
   local gl = gui.gl
   twgl.resizeCanvasToDisplaySize(gl.canvas,dpr)
   gl.viewport(0, 0, gl.canvas.width, gl.canvas.height)
   
   gui.t = (gui.t or 0) + 16
   gui.uniforms.time = gui.t * 0.001
   gui.uniforms.resolution[1] = gl.canvas.width
   gui.uniforms.resolution[2] = gl.canvas.height

   gl.useProgram(gui.programInfo.program)
   twgl.setBuffersAndAttributes(gl,
      gui.programInfo,
      gui.bufferInfo
   )
   twgl.setUniforms(gui.programInfo, gui.uniforms)
   twgl.drawBufferInfo(gl, gui.bufferInfo)

   if s.root.processQueue then
      local w,h = gui.cnv.width, gui.cnv.height
      if h==0 or w==0 then w,h = 1,1 end
      s.root.pushEvent{type=\"update view\", xOverY=w/h}
      s.root.glyphInfo = gui.jsonTbl
      s.root.drawListRefresh()
      s.root.processQueue()
      s.root.update()

--      s.root.drawListRefresh()
      if gui.atlasImg.complete then
         gl.blendFunc(gl.SRC_ALPHA, gl.ONE)
         gl.enable(gl.BLEND)
         gl.disable(gl.DEPTH_TEST)
   
         local list = s.root.drawCharList
         local pos = gui.textBufferInfo.attribs.position
         twgl.setAttribInfoBufferFromArray(
            gl,pos,list.positions
         )
         local texCoord = gui.textBufferInfo.attribs.aCoord
         twgl.setAttribInfoBufferFromArray(
            gl,texCoord,list.chars
         )
         local ch = list.chars
         gui.textBufferInfo.numElements = #ch / 2

         gl.useProgram(gui.textProgramInfo.program)
         twgl.setBuffersAndAttributes(gl,
            gui.textProgramInfo,
            gui.textBufferInfo
         )

         if not gui.atlasTexLoaded then
            --[[]]
            twgl.setTextureFromElement(gl,
               gui.atlasTex,gui.atlasImg,{min=gl.LINEAR}
            )
            --]]
            --[[
            twgl.setTextureFromElement(gl,
               gui.atlasTex,gui.atlasImg
            )
            --]]
            gui.atlasTexLoaded = true
         end
         gui.textUniforms = {
            time = gui.t,
            samp = gui.atlasTex
         }
         twgl.setUniforms(
            gui.textProgramInfo,
            gui.textUniforms
         )
         twgl.drawBufferInfo(gl,gui.textBufferInfo)
         gl.enable(gl.DEPTH_TEST)
         gl.disable(gl.BLEND)
      end
